  "prompt": "How long can a milkshake last out of the fridge?",
  "response": "The duration a milkshake can last out of the fridge depends on various factors, including the ambient temperature and ingredients used. Generally, a milkshake can begin to spoil after about one to two hours at room temperature. Dairy products, especially, are prone to bacterial growth when kept out of refrigeration. For optimal safety and taste, it is best to consume the milkshake within this time frame or store it in the refrigerator to keep it fresh.",
